The United States and China have formally joined the Paris Agreement on climate change, marking a significant step towards the agreement entering into force this year. The leaders also affirmed their commitment to work together on other climate-related issues such as phasing down the consumption and production of hydrofluorocarbons (HFCs) and reducing carbon emissions from international aviation. Both countries also announced their intention to publish their respective long-term low greenhouse gas emission development strategies under the Paris Agreement. In addition, the United States and China committed to deepen their bilateral climate cooperation through various frameworks and upcoming events.